What you are doing is not a proper A star algorithm.

    Collections.sort(successors);

You shouldn&#39;t do that. In A star you always consider all the successors. You needn&#39;t worry about the order- the priority queue will take care of that. However, adding this line increases the complexity of the algorithm.

